  <description><![CDATA[ 




<p>This tutorial will help you get started with contributing to <a href="https://blog.integrationfest.in">Integration Blog</a> series.</p>
<section id="pre-requisites" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="pre-requisites">Pre-Requisites</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://drive.google.com">Google Drive</a></li>
<li>Familiarity with <a href="https://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/authoring_basics.html">Markdown</a></li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="authoring" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="authoring">Authoring</h2>
<p>Author the blog post in markdown format.</p>
</section>
<section id="uploading" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="uploading">Uploading</h2>
<ul>
<li>Open the <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1do8dJdrgK-cOa02tDJueM7PoKuwKqT5M?usp=sharing">Google Drive</a> folder</li>
<li>In the <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/18UgrebGacbEO7wlfrTRoqBttEIx-y3Fs?usp=drive_link">Blog Writups</a> subfolder, upload the Markdown <code>.md</code> file.</li>
</ul>
</section>
<section id="publishing" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="publishing">Publishing</h2>
<ul>
<li>Inform the Integration DIC team about the article, and request inclusion.</li>
<li>The post would be added to the site soon.</li>
</ul>


</section>

